item.title: [HIVE-20935] Upload of llap package tarball fails in EC2 causing LLAP service start failure
item.description:
Even though package dir is defined as below (with a / at the end) -

LLAP_PACKAGE_DIR = ".yarn/package/LLAP/";

copyLocalFileToHdfs API fails to create the dir hierarchy of .yarn/package/LLAP/ first and then copy the file under it. It instead uploads the file under .yarn/package with name LLAP.
item.summary: Upload of llap package tarball fails in EC2 causing LLAP service start failure

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: Uploaded a patch to explicitly create the dir before trying to copy the file.
